## Quality checks

Generic to any production project.

- [ ] No secrets committed (scan for `KEY=`, `sk_live_`, `password =`, etc.)
- [ ] All list endpoints paginated (default limit)
- [ ] No `SELECT *` in queries; columns named explicitly
- [ ] No binary blobs in list/poll endpoints (use `has_<field>` booleans)
- [ ] Health check endpoint returns 200
- [ ] UI discloses backend activity: every async action shows a visible state (loading / progress / success / error). No silent fetches, no spinners without context, no failed requests that disappear into the console. The user can always tell what the API/backend/console is doing without opening devtools.

## Deploy checks (local pre-deploy)

- [ ] Build succeeds (`{{build_cmd}}`)
- [ ] Type check passes (if typed)
- [ ] Tests pass (including the failing-test-first / TDD red→green test for the current task)

## Deployed-env checks  (re-walked by /bencium-deploy against {{deploy_url}})

Each item here is a feature contract that **must pass against the live URL**, not just the local build. `/bencium-verify` skips these with reason `awaiting post-deploy smoke`; `/bencium-deploy` Step 5.5 SMOKE evaluates them and refuses success on any FAIL.

- [deployed] {{product_check_1}} works at {{deploy_url}} (end-to-end, real network, real env vars)
- [deployed] No console errors on the deployed page load (`curl` HTML + check for embedded error markers, or a Playwright smoke if available)
- [deployed] UI loading/error states are wired and visible on the deployed env (no "works on localhost only" regressions from env or build-mode differences)

Add or remove checks as the project grows. Retros (`/bencium-retro`) will propose new checks when failures happen — especially for any local-pass / deployed-fail divergence.
